						<summary>

						<p>This inscription refers to a gift of 20 <hi rend="italic">kalañju</hi> gold for burning a lamp in the temple of Tattēri mahādēva of Kaḷattūr by Kāḍupaṭṭi Kāraḷaiyuḍaiya Kaḍupaṭṭi-Vayiriyappar of Chō[ḻa]nāḍu in Paiyūr Iḷaṅgōṭṭam. The money was entrusted with the assembly of Pañjiṟaikaḷattūr in Kaḍigai nāḍu a sub-division of Dāmaṟkōṭṭam along with the annual supervision committee <hi rend="italic">(Samvatsaravāriyam).</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
